Schmitz, 1927
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[835,1474,1485,1850]" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">
The treatment of 
<taxonomicName authority="Schmitz, 1927" authorityName="Schmitz" authorityYear="1927" box="[1056,1419,1485,1509]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Abaristophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1056,1230,1486,1509]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Abaristophora</emphasis>
Schmitz, 1927
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Schmitz, 1939" authorityName="Schmitz" authorityYear="1939" box="[835,1161,1516,1540]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Abaristophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Antipodiphora">
<emphasis box="[835,992,1517,1540]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Antipodiphora</emphasis>
Schmitz, 1939
</taxonomicName>
as distinct genera was long disputed (Schmitz, 1939; 
<bibRefCitation author="Borgmeier, T" box="[1122,1309,1547,1571]" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" pagination="1 - 256" refId="ref2580" refString="Borgmeier, T., 1963. Revision of the North American phorid flies. Part 1. The Phorinae, Aenigmatiinae and Metopininae, except Megaselia (Diptera, Phoridae). Studia Entomologia, 6: 1 - 256." type="journal article" year="1963">Borgmeier, 1963</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Brown, B" box="[1323,1469,1547,1571]" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" pagination="307 - 322" refId="ref2622" refString="Brown, B. V., 1988. Additions to the phorid chapter in the Manual of Nearctic Diptera, Volume 2 (Diptera: Phoridae). Canadian Entomologist, 120: 307 - 322." type="journal article" year="1988">Brown, 1988</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Brown, B" box="[835,890,1578,1602]" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" pagination="1 - 144" refId="ref2660" refString="Brown, B. V., 1992. Generic revision of Phoridae of the Nearctic Region and phylogenetic classification of Phoridae, Sciadoceridae and Ironomyiidae (Diptera: Phoridea). Memoirs of the Entomological Society of Canada, 164: 1 - 144." type="journal article" year="1992">1992</bibRefCitation>
) until Disney &amp; Ross (1997) treated 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schmitz" authorityYear="1939" box="[1289,1445,1579,1602]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Abaristophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Antipodiphora">
<emphasis box="[1289,1445,1579,1602]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Antipodiphora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schmitz" authorityYear="1927" box="[998,1154,1610,1633]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Abaristophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[998,1154,1610,1633]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Abaristophora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Nakayama &amp; Shima (2006) gave detailed information on the status of each genus and the relation to its closest relative genus 
<taxonomicName box="[1267,1386,1672,1695]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Borophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1267,1386,1672,1695]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Borophaga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Before this article, 12 species were known worldwide (Table 1.). The species of subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schmitz" authorityYear="1927" box="[1104,1260,1733,1756]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Abaristophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1104,1260,1733,1756]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Abaristophora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are restricted to the northern hemisphere except the undescribed species in 
<bibRefCitation author="Brown, B" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" pagination="1 - 144" refId="ref2660" refString="Brown, B. V., 1992. Generic revision of Phoridae of the Nearctic Region and phylogenetic classification of Phoridae, Sciadoceridae and Ironomyiidae (Diptera: Phoridea). Memoirs of the Entomological Society of Canada, 164: 1 - 144." type="journal article" year="1992">Brown (1992)</bibRefCitation>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[977,1089,1794,1818]" name="Venezuela" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
, while the species of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schmitz" authorityYear="1939" box="[835,991,1827,1850]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Abaristophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Antipodiphora">
<emphasis box="[835,991,1827,1850]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Antipodiphora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
seems to have an Oriental distribution.
</paragraph>
